parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Excessive RTV Sealant in Engine Oil
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The excessive RTV sealant in the engine oil can cause oil starvation, leading to catastrophic engine failure, stalling, and potentially causing accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: Traces of silicone or RTV sealant found on the dipstick
or in the engine oil; engine stalling; warning lamps on the dashboard; restricted oil flow; premature engine failure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel injector can cause fuel to leak and flood the cylinder chamber, leading to engine stalling, and potentially causing accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: Strong scent of gas when opening the door; difficulty starting the engine; warning lamps on the dashboard; engine stalling.
